dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.cbe.root.ManagedEntity
dataStructure.description:
This is an abstract base class that is used to represent entities in a managed environment that have the following semantics in common: (1) a ManagedBusinessEntity owns or is otherwise responsible for them, (2) management of the entity is critical for providing a service and/or maintaining the environment, and (3) the entity is "important" from a management point-of-view. As such, it is a point at which semantically important relationships can be created; this avoids duplicating these relationships on multiple subclasses as well as forcing ManagedObject to support these relationships.

This entity is abstract

This entity is optional
dataStructure.label: ManagedEntity
